.TH GlusterFS 8 "Clusta Filesystem" "18 March 2010" "Glusta Inc."
.SH NAME
mount.glusterfs - script ta mount natizzle GlusterFS volume
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mount -t glusterfs
.I [-o <options>] <volumeserver>:<volumeid> <mountpoint>
.TP
.B mount -t glusterfs
.I [-o <options>] <path/to/volumefile> <mountpoint>
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
This tool is part of \fBglusterfs\fR(8) package, which is used ta mount using
GlusterFS natizzle binary.

\fBmount.glusterfs\fR  is meant ta be used by tha mount(8) command fo' mounting
natizzle GlusterFS client. This subcommand, however, can also be used as a
standalone command wit limited functionality.

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
.SS "Basic options"
.PP
.TP
\fBlog\-file=\fRLOG-FILE
File ta use fo' loggin [default:/var/log/glusterfs/glusterfs.log]
.TP
\fBlog\-level=\fRLOG-LEVEL
Loggin severity.  Valid options is TRACE, DEBUG, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
INFO n' NONE [default: INFO]
.TP
\fBro\fR
Mount tha filesystem read-only
.PP
.SS "Advanced options"
.PP
.TP
\fBvolfile\-id=\fRKEY
Volume key or name of tha volume file ta be fetched from server
.TP
\fBtransport=\fRTRANSPORT-TYPE
Transhiznit type ta git volume file from server [default: tcp]
.TP
\fBvolume\-name=\fRVOLUME-NAME
Volume name ta be used fo' MOUNT-POINT [default: top most volume in
VOLUME-FILE]
.TP
\fBdirect\-io\-mode=\fRdisable
Disable direct I/O mode up in fuse kernel module
.TP
.PP
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/fstab
A typical GlusterFS entry up in /etc/fstab be lookin like below

server1.gluster.com:mirror  /mnt/mirror  glusterfs  log-file=/var/log/mirror.vol,ro,defaults   0  0

.TP
.I /etc/mtab
An example entry of a GlusterFS mountpoint up in /etc/mtab be lookin like below

mirror.vol /mnt/glusterfs fuse.glusterfs rw,allow_other,default_permissions,max_read=131072 0 0

